"]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Threlkeld was born about 1220, in Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. He married Isabel de Hastings about 1250, in Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1280, in his hometown, at the age of 62."},"et":{"ABT    1220–ABT    1280":"umbes 1220–umbes 1280","1210–1260":"1210–1260","1258–1290":"1258–1290","1220–1280":"1220–1280","1258":"1258","ABT    1220":"umbes 1220","1210":"1210","ABT    1250":"umbes 1250","1220":"1220","ABT    1260":"umbes 1260","ABT    1280":"umbes 1280","1260":"1260","ABT 1280":"umbes 1280","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Westmoreland,England":"Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Threlkeld, Cumberland, England":"Threlkeld, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT    1220–ABT    1280":"noin 1220–noin 1280","1210–1260":"1210–1260","1258–1290":"1258–1290","1220–1280":"1220–1280","1258":"1258","ABT    1220":"noin 1220","1210":"1210","ABT    1250":"noin 1250","1220":"1220","ABT    1260":"noin 1260","ABT    1280":"noin 1280","1260":"1260","ABT 1280":"noin 1280","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Westmorland, England, United Kingdo